I'm not sure if my data will be that helpful in demonstrating in detecting chills from this kind of stimulus. The music selected didn't really illicit any strong emotions or response for me. I experienced getting the chills when the sensory cap was being placed. The conductive gel was cold which triggered the effect. A tingling sensation on my head.

For audio perspective, I think the Protocol 004 had a bigger effect. There was rain/storm music playing. I got the chills during that experiment. The visuals were really cool as well.

I think for me, ASMR sounds like crinkling, tapping, etc sounds would be more effective for me personally audio wise.

I feel a lot of who we are is also shaped by what makes us up genetically; on both sides of the family i had very spiritual and artistic people. I consider myself very healthy and thank God and life for allowing me pretty much do and experiment or experience different things without much physical difficulty, enjoying being tall, enjoying my sense of sight and hearing, being able to walk and run, drive a car, speak two languages and have a multi cultural view of things which i think enriches this whole thing. All of this makes me highly motivated to keep pursuing the artistic and business projects that i am attracted to, even thought i have made many mistakes that have derailed me from achieving some of those things. Or the way i see it, if the creative sensibility does not get involved in this kind of search, then life becomes difficult.

The work situation is a little more challenging for me since a connection between people bring more meaning to my life than "keeping it professional", that's why sometimes it's hard for me to focus on money/tasks because I get distracted on human feelings, connecting to people, and even people watching. column345: I see myself with a Buddhist/liberal Christian perspective influenced by being sober & in recovery. I see myself as inter-connected with everyone and everything. I am a spiritual being having a human experience, and I don't completely understand it. I meditate, pray, try to be of service go to recovery and meditation meetings daily. But I also made a lot of mistakes. I owe a lot of money to the IRS, and my mom is helping me and my daughter financially. I am getting back to work as a substitute teacher, but I used to teach full time and earn a good salary. Sometimes I feel as if I've wasted my resources and opportunities; but I think I am getting better at accepting my life where I am and enjoying my life, my eleven-year-old child, boyfriend, friends, family, and communities. I'm glad I studied dance at UCLA and spent many days reading, watching dance and theater, doing and teaching yoga, and times I have had the opportunity to travel. I'm grateful I have a child and pets, see myself as part of a community and in a relationship with God/spirituality. I am so grateful for music, dance, and the beauty of nature. I'm glad I have a master's degree in education and taught full time for ten years -- mostly as an English teacher. I wish I hadn't been so stressed, but I think if I teach full time again (hopefully), I can learn, change and grow in positive ways. I enjoy my life and teaching much more now that I am sober and have an active meditation and prayer life. I'm glad I can even now contribute in small ways financially politically and in my recovery work, and in big ways in terms of service, care and influence. I'm grateful to be a part of life -- interacting and connecting with other beings.

column345:
I am an artist, visually and musically! I see and hear the world differently than the average person. I see images everyday, everywhere I go, and sometimes I just take a mental picture if I can't capture a shot quick enough!

Even musically, sometimes I put certain sounds together and find myself slipping into Hypnosis by how the sounds are all interacting with each other!

I see faces when I look at things most of the times...Recently, I was outside enjoying the weather and looking up at the sky and I started seeing the most beautiful glitter in the sky and it felt and seemed to be so real! 

I've also seen shadow people, and apparations and can feel when something supernatural is around me, and/or if the energy in a certain space has changed I can fel that as well.

There are also times that I could just be walking down the street and suddenly feel like I've stepped into a movie, sometimes I can look at a person and get a glimpse into what their life is like!
